2. Iterate through the lowercase string and count the occurrences of each character using a 26-element array (one for each letter of the alphabet).
3. Iterate through the lowercase string again and build a substring for each character that occurs more than once.
4. Add the built substrings to a list and return the list.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because it only iterates through the string once. The space complexity is O(n) because we use an array to store the count of each character and a list to store the repeated substrings.

